# Testing & Verification

**Rationale:** infrastructure has no unit-testable runtime; the plan is the test
surface. The gate ladder orders checks from cheapest to most expensive so failures
surface early and every gate is deterministic.

## Gate ladder

| Gate | Command | Catches | Needs cloud? |
|---|---|---|---|
| 1 Format | `terraform fmt -check -recursive` | Style drift | No |
| 2 Validate | `terraform validate` (per root, `-backend=false`) | Type errors, bad references | No |
| 3 Lint | `tflint --recursive` | Deprecated syntax, provider misuse, unused declarations | No |
| 4 Security scan | `trivy config .` (or checkov) | Known misconfiguration patterns | No |
| 5 Unit test | `terraform test` with provider `mock_provider` | Module logic: size maps, flavor dispatch, validation | No |
| 6 Policy | `conftest test plan.json -p policies/` | Constitution violations on the actual diff | Plan only |
| 7 Plan review | human + `review-plan` skill on plan JSON | Everything else: replacements, spec drift | Plan only |

Gates 1–5 run on every commit; 6–7 on every PR. **Nothing beyond plan runs outside CI.**

## Makefile contract (every consumer repo)

Every stack repo must provide a root **`Makefile`** with these targets:

| Target | Purpose |
|--------|---------|
| `setup` | One-time tool verification (`terraform` required; `tflint`, `trivy`, `conftest` noted if missing) |
| `check` | Offline gates 1–4: fmt, validate, lint, scan — no cloud credentials |
| `test` | Gate 5: `terraform test` on module `tests/` directories |
| `plan` | Gates 6–7 input: init + plan per `ENV`, emit `plan.json`, run conftest when policies exist |

Use `ENV=<env>` (default `dev`) for `preflight` and `plan`. Exact implementation
lives in the consumer repo — not in this constitution.

`make check` green is the precondition for opening a PR.

## terraform test rules

1. Every shared module ships `tests/*.tftest.hcl` covering: each supported flavor
   plans successfully; each size profile resolves; invalid inputs fail validation.

```hcl
# modules/<component>/tests/flavors.tftest.hcl
mock_provider "azurerm" {}

run "managed_flavor_plans" {
  command = plan
  variables { flavor = "managed", size_profile = "m" }
  assert {
    condition     = length(azurerm_postgresql_flexible_server.this) > 0
    error_message = "managed flavor must create the flexible server resource"
  }
}
```

2. Mocked tests verify **logic**, not cloud behavior. Live verification against a
   sandbox subscription/account is a separate, manually-triggered flow
   (`tests/verify/`) — never in CI, never against shared envs.
3. A module PR that changes behavior without touching its tests is incomplete.
